   <dictum id="٤٣٤٦٤">
      <text>
         <ar>رَمَى الْقَوْمُ</ar>
         <free>The people went forth</free>
      </text>
      <igt>
         <t>
           <ar>رَمَى</ar>
           <en>threw</en>
         </t>
         <t>
            <ar>الْقَوْمُ</ar>
         </t>
      </igt>
      <sidecomment>
        Lit: “the people threw”.  The <ar>ى</ar>
        of <ar>رَمَى</ar> is dropped because it is a
        <ar>حرف ساكن</ar> “static term” followed
        by a second static term (the lām of <ar>الْقَوْمُ</ar>),
        so it is pronounced “rama”, not “ramā”.
      </sidecomment>
   </dictum>
